{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17537091","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17537091"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:13:29+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:13:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15902"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15902","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15902"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.2,0.65,0.01,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8593"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63066"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8593","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8593"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15902"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48517"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"37"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1063"},{"type":"tags","id":"1075"},{"type":"tags","id":"3496"},{"type":"tags","id":"4648"},{"type":"tags","id":"4772"},{"type":"tags","id":"4790"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4983"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11643"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20595"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36982"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63066","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/63066"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 24-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-week history of intense itching in his genital area, which is worse at night. He has had six sexual partners in the last four months, and has ongoing regular sexual contact with one partner who reports similar symptoms. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There are erythematous papules and excoriations on the penis and scrotum, and in the inguinal creases. There are many grey, thread-like lines visible around the papules. Similar lesions are noted on his hands.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate treatment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Topical hydrocortisone cream","Intramuscular benzathine penicillin","Topical permethrin cream","Oral antihistamines","Topical clotrimazole cream"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with classic features of scabies infestation caused by the mite \u003Cem\u003ESarcoptes scabiei\u003C/em\u003E. The diagnosis is supported by the characteristic intense nocturnal pruritus, typical distribution of lesions including the genitals and skin folds, and the presence of burrows. The fact that his partner has similar symptoms further supports the diagnosis, as scabies is highly contagious through prolonged skin-to-skin contact.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETopical permethrin cream\u003C/strong\u003E is the first-line treatment for scabies. It should be applied to the entire body from the neck down and left on for 8-14 hours before washing off. Treatment should be repeated after one week. All close contacts should be treated simultaneously, even if asymptomatic, to prevent reinfestation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETopical hydrocortisone cream\u003C/strong\u003E might temporarily relieve itching but would not address the underlying infestation. It should not be used as primary treatment, however can be useful in managing symptoms after permethrin treatment has been administered. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral antihistamines\u003C/strong\u003E may help with symptom control but do not treat the underlying cause. They can be used as an adjunct to permethrin treatment to help control pruritus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETopical clotrimazole cream\u003C/strong\u003E is an antifungal medication used for fungal infections such as tinea cruris. While genital itching can be caused by fungal infections, the presence of burrows and nocturnal itching are pathognomonic for scabies.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBenzathine penicillin\u003C/strong\u003E is the treatment of choice for syphilis but would not be effective against scabies mites. Whilst syphilis can present with a rash on the palms, the genital lesions seen noted are not typical of a chancre.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAfter treatment, itching may persist for several weeks due to a hypersensitivity reaction to the dead mites. Patients should be advised about this to prevent unnecessary retreatment. All clothing, bedding, and towels should be washed in hot water (\u0026gt;60\u00b0C) and dried in a hot dryer, or sealed in plastic bags for at least 72 hours, as the mites can survive for 48-72 hours without human contact.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Scabies typically presents with intense nocturnal pruritus and characteristic burrows in the web spaces, wrists, and genital area.","Permethrin 5% cream is the first-line treatment for scabies in patients over 2 months of age.","All sexual partners and household contacts should be treated simultaneously to prevent reinfestation.","Clothes and bedding must be washed in hot water (\u003E60\u00b0C) to prevent reinfestation."],"references":["Gopinath H, Karthikeyan K. Genital scabies: Haven of an unwelcome guest. Indian J Sex Transm Dis AIDS. 2020 Jan-Jun;41(1):10-16. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7529175/","Ectoparasites - STI Guidelines Australia [Internet]. 2021. Available at: https://sti.guidelines.org.au/sexually-transmissible-infections/ectoparasites/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48517"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15902"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48517","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48517"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-19T22:01:00+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-19T22:02:25+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8593"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63066"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"37","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/37"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf46","name":"Sexual Health","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"crea